<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Sun, 05 Jul 2026 13:04:16 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>17 种人体组织 DNA 甲基化衰老特征的荟萃分析</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/meta-analysis-of-dna-methylation-aging-signatures-in-17-human-tissues</link><description>Jacques 及其同事提出了 DNA 甲基化衰老的跨组织荟萃分析，揭示了保守的衰老特征和可修改的基因簇。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/meta-analysis-of-dna-methylation-aging-signatures-in-17-human-tissues.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 05 Jul 2026 13:04:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/meta-analysis-of-dna-methylation-aging-signatures-in-17-human-tissues</guid></item><item><title>科学家现在可以研究黑洞的事件视界</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/scientists-can-now-study-the-event-horizons-of-black-holes</link><description>他们打造了宇宙中最极端的引力实验室&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/scientists-can-now-study-the-event-horizons-of-black-holes.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 05 Jul 2026 12:49:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/scientists-can-now-study-the-event-horizons-of-black-holes</guid></item><item><title>早期卵巢癌的微创手术、术中包膜破裂和生存</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/minimally-invasive-surgery-intraoperative-capsule-rupture-and-survival-in-early-ovarian-cancer</link><description>该队列研究探讨了 I 期卵巢癌患者的微创手术、术中包膜破裂与总生存期之间的关系。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/minimally-invasive-surgery-intraoperative-capsule-rupture-and-survival-in-early-ovarian-cancer.png" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 05 Jul 2026 12:34:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/minimally-invasive-surgery-intraoperative-capsule-rupture-and-survival-in-early-ovarian-cancer</guid></item><item><title>用于临床试验的免疫衰老生物标志物</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/immune-aging-biomarkers-for-clinical-trials</link><description>作者提出了一个选择适合老年科学临床试验的免疫衰老生物标志物的框架，以及生物标志物开发的转化路线图，以支持下一代免疫衰老临床研究。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/immune-aging-biomarkers-for-clinical-trials.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 05 Jul 2026 12:19:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/immune-aging-biomarkers-for-clinical-trials</guid></item><item><title>团队利用3D打印开发能量增加七倍的锌离子混合电池</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/team-uses-3d-printing-to-develop-zinc-ion-hybrid-battery-with-seven-times-more-energy</link><description>存储太阳能和风能以满足电网日益增长的电力需求，需要能够快速供电、快速充电并以低成本持续数十年的设备。加州大学洛杉矶分校领导的一项新研究发现了一种可以满足所有这些标准的技术：带有 3D 打印电极的锌离子混合电池，其存储的电量是类似混合电池的七倍以上。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/team-uses-3d-printing-to-develop-zinc-ion-hybrid-battery-with-seven-times-more-energy.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 05 Jul 2026 12:04:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/team-uses-3d-printing-to-develop-zinc-ion-hybrid-battery-with-seven-times-more-energy</guid></item><item><title>光开关唤醒沉睡的癌细胞，使它们再次变得脆弱</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/light-switch-wakes-sleeping-cancer-cells-and-makes-them-vulnerable-again</link><description>一些癌细胞可以进入休眠、类似睡眠的状态，这有助于它们在治疗中存活下来。这些细胞不再继续生长和分裂，而是变得基本上不活跃，从而使它们能够避免许多抗癌药物的作用。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/light-switch-wakes-sleeping-cancer-cells-and-makes-them-vulnerable-again.webp" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 05 Jul 2026 11:49:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/light-switch-wakes-sleeping-cancer-cells-and-makes-them-vulnerable-again</guid></item><item><title>美国宇航局测试月球和火星漫游车的先进能力</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/nasa-testing-advanced-capabilities-for-moon-mars-rovers</link><description>在南加州科罗拉多沙漠一片荒凉的土地上，一辆紧凑型四轮漫游车最近行驶了 16 英里（26 公里），而跟踪它的工程师团队只对其进行了极少的干预。该原型被称为 ERNEST（用于导航极端倾斜地形的探索漫游车），美国宇航局正在使用该原型来提高机器人自主性和穿越具有挑战性的景观的能力。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/nasa-testing-advanced-capabilities-for-moon-mars-rovers.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 05 Jul 2026 11:34:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/nasa-testing-advanced-capabilities-for-moon-mars-rovers</guid></item><item><title>声波可以为受人脑启发的新型芯片提供动力</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/soundwaves-could-power-a-new-kind-of-chip-inspired-by-the-human-brain</link><description>神经形态计算是一种模仿人脑工作方式的计算方法。我们的灰质是大自然的奇迹，能够以令人难以置信的能源效率处理大量数据。虽然现代人工智能硬件在处理复杂任务方面变得越来越出色，但它会消耗大量能源。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/soundwaves-could-power-a-new-kind-of-chip-inspired-by-the-human-brain2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 05 Jul 2026 11:19:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/soundwaves-could-power-a-new-kind-of-chip-inspired-by-the-human-brain</guid></item><item><title>临床试验发现，常见的粘液清除疗法无法帮助 ICU 患者呼吸更顺畅，并可能造成伤害</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/common-mucus-clearing-treatments-dont-help-icu-patients-breathe-easier-and-may-cause-harm-clinical-trial-finds</link><description>对于因急性呼吸衰竭而呼吸困难的患者来说，清除气道中的粘液是治疗的常规部分。粘液活性剂广泛用于此目的。但经过多年的临床使用，仍然存在一个问题：粘液活性剂真的有帮助吗？ &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/common-mucus-clearing-treatments-dont-help-icu-patients-breathe-easier-and-may-cause-harm-clinical-trial-finds2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 05 Jul 2026 11:04:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/common-mucus-clearing-treatments-dont-help-icu-patients-breathe-easier-and-may-cause-harm-clinical-trial-finds</guid></item><item><title>人类红细胞的形成没有小鼠模型中所见的中央“枢纽”，颠覆了我们对生理学的理解</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/human-red-blood-cells-form-without-central-hub-seen-in-mouse-models-upending-understanding-of-our-physiology</link><description>一项新的研究表明，西北医学科学家发现，人体最基本的生物过程之一——红细胞的生成方式——在人类中的运作方式与之前认为的不同&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/human-red-blood-cells-form-without-central-hub-seen-in-mouse-models-upending-understanding-of-our-physiology2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 05 Jul 2026 10:49:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/human-red-blood-cells-form-without-central-hub-seen-in-mouse-models-upending-understanding-of-our-physiology</guid></item></channel></rss>